# SVG overlay child components

**Editor chrome** overlays (`SelectionOverlayComponent`, `PathNodeOverlayComponent`, and future extractees) are Angular child components hosted on SVG `<g>` inside the highlight overlay. The host `<g>` is created in the parent canvas template and is in the SVG namespace; **template children of the child component are not** — Angular compiles them as XHTML unless you prefix tags with `svg:`.

Without `svg:`, elements exist in the DOM but do not paint (zero bounding box, handles invisible). This regressed when overlays were extracted in commit `8afe5a0`.

## Component shape

- Host selector on an SVG group: `selector: 'g[app-*-overlay]'`
- `NO_ERRORS_SCHEMA` on the component (SVG tags in template)
- Presentation logic stays in the overlay; geometry/state comes from canvas via `input()` and typed models (e.g. `path-node-overlay.model.ts`)
- Bind through `SvgCanvasEditorChromeFacade` in `svg-canvas.component.html`, not new domain services

## Template rules

1. **Prefix every SVG element** in the child template with `svg:` (`svg:circle`, `svg:line`, `svg:rect`, `svg:path`, `svg:g`).
2. **Bind presentation attributes** with `[attr.*]` (`[attr.fill]`, `[attr.stroke]`, `[attr.r]`, `[attr.cx]`, etc.) — not bare `fill="..."` / `r="4"`.
3. **Stacking**: keep overlay `<g app-*-overlay>` after pen previews/ghosts in `svg-canvas.component.html` so affordances paint on top.

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD — XHTML namespace; invisible in overlay SVG -->
<circle
  class="selection-resize-handle"
  [attr.cx]="hr.x"
  [attr.cy]="hr.y"
  r="6"
  fill="#ffffff"/>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<svg:circle
  class="selection-resize-handle"
  [attr.cx]="hr.x"
  [attr.cy]="hr.y"
  [attr.r]="handleRadius()"
  [attr.fill]="'#ffffff'"
  [attr.stroke]="'#2196F3'"
  [attr.stroke-width]="2"
  [attr.vector-effect]="'non-scaling-stroke'"/>
```

Markup **directly** in `svg-canvas.component.html` inside `<svg class="highlight-overlay">` does not need `svg:` — only **child component** templates do.

## Tests

Add or extend a namespace probe spec when creating a new overlay component:

```typescript
expect(handle?.namespaceURI).toBe('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg');
```

See `selection-overlay.namespace.probe.spec.ts` and `path-node-overlay.namespace.probe.spec.ts`.
